title: The Boas Mathematics Library: Libraries - Northwestern University
content: The Math Library is only accessible to Northwestern community members with an active Wildcard, with no staff assistance. The building is open for 24 hours with keycard access for Northwestern Mathematics and Statistics graduate students and faculty. SEE HOURS Lunt Hall Level 1, 2033 Sheridan Road, Evanston, IL 60208. See an online map. Call 847-491-7627 or email mathlib@northwestern.edu.  The Mathematics Library is under the supervision of Becca Greenstein, who can provide research assistance and answer questions. Contact Becca by email at rgreenst@northwestern.edu or phone at 847-467-6606. For tutoring and advising assistance, see the Math Department website.
